steps.instruction:
### Prep
- Finely chop the shallots
- Finely chop the parsley

### Steps
1. Preheat oven to 425°F
2. Season roast on all sides with 1 tablespoon oil and 1 tablespoon steak seasoning
3. Place roast on rack in roasting pan (wash hands)
4. Place roast in oven; cook 20 minutes or until browned
5. Reduce oven to 350°F; cook 1–1 1/2 hours and until roast is 125°F (for medium rare; warm red center), 130°F (medium; warm pink center), or up to 170°F (well done)
6. Use a meat thermometer to accurately ensure doneness
7. Transfer roast to cutting board; let stand 10–15 minutes before slicing
    - Temperature will rise 5–10°F during this time
8. Chop shallots and parsley
9.   Preheat large sauté pan on medium 2–3 minutes
10. Place remaining 1 tablespoon oil in pan, then add shallots; cook 1 minute to soften
11. Reduce heat to medium-low; add wine and cook until liquid is reduced by about two-thirds
12. Stir in cream and remaining 1/4 teaspoon steak seasoning; simmer 2–3 minutes or until sauce begins to thicken
13. Remove pan from heat; whisk in cheese until smooth
14. Stir parsley into sauce. Slice roast and serve with sauce
